-- Total Wins Bulgaria Black Sea Deep-Water Drilling Permit
-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   K o n s t a n t i n o v a
-- 2012-07-12T16:44:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-12/total-wins-bulgaria-black-sea-deep-water-drilling-permit-1-.html
Total SA (FP)  won a permit to explore for
natural gas in the deep waters of the  Black Sea  off the
Bulgarian coast, Energy, Economy and Tourism Minister Delyan Dobrev told reporters in Sofia today.  Total competed with  Exxon Mobil Corp. (XOM)  and  Melrose Resources
Plc (MRS)  for the permit explore the Khan Asparuh block near the
northern border with Romania, which is for five years, including
the initial drilling, he said.  Austria’s  OMV AG (OMV)  and Spain’s Repsol SA are partnering with
Total on the permit, Austria Press Agency reported, citing the
ministry.  OMV in February said that it had found gas in a Black Sea
well in neighboring Romania in what might be its biggest find
ever.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elizabeth Konstantinova in Sofia at 
